Top view, including handles; the tondo depicts an amorous youth, holding a cup and a staff, hugging a female lyre player
Photograph by Maria Daniels, courtesy of the Musée du Louvre

Close-up view of the tondo: a girl, wearing a medium-sleeved chiton and a narrow stephane, stands profile to the right, holding a lyre in her left hand and a plectrum in her right hand; a youth, wearing short pointed boots, a himation slung over his right shoulder, and a narrow taenia on his head, stands to her left (his face is shown in a rare frontal view), wraps his right arm around her shoulders, and holds a cup and a knotty staff or cane in his outstretched left hand
Photograph by Maria Daniels, courtesy of the Musée du Louvre
Detail of the tondo, top: the upper bodies of a youth and a girl, and the objects that they hold
Photograph by Maria Daniels, courtesy of the Musée du Louvre
Detail of the tondo, right: a girl and a youth embracing her
Photograph by Maria Daniels, courtesy of the Musée du Louvre
Bottom view, including handles: exterior scenes of love making
Photograph by Maria Daniels, courtesy of the Musée du Louvre
Close-up view of side A, from below: couples engaged in erotic acts
Photograph by Maria Daniels, courtesy of the Musée du Louvre

Detail of side A, left: the passive (female) partner in a tergo intercourse, nude, crouching on the ground, profile to the right; a bearded, nude male, running to the left, pursued by a sexually excited, nude youth, holding a lamp in his outstretched right hand
Photograph by Maria Daniels, courtesy of the Musée du Louvre
Detail of side A, center: a sexually excited, nude youth, running profile to the left, holding a lamp in his outstretched right hand and a lamp stand, behind him, in his left hand;
Photograph by Maria Daniels, courtesy of the Musée du Louvre

Detail of side A, right: a heterosexual couple engaging in oral intercourse; a nude youth kneels to the right, on a cushion, reaches his left hand ahead (to steady himself?) and holds a rhyton behind him, in his right hand; the short-haired, nude woman, wearing a red ribbon in her hair, crouches on the ground before him
Photograph by Maria Daniels, courtesy of the Musée du Louvre

Detail of side A, far right: a heterosexual couple engaging in oral intercourse; a nude youth kneels to the right, on a cushion, reaches his left hand ahead (to steady himself?) and holds a rhyton behind him, in his right hand; the short-haired, nude woman, wearing a red ribbon in her hair, crouches on the ground before him
Photograph by Maria Daniels, courtesy of the Musée du Louvre
Close-up view of side B, from below: erotic acts
Photograph by Maria Daniels, courtesy of the Musée du Louvre

Detail of side B, left: a menage à trois; a nude youth, standing profile to the right, inserts his member in the mouth of a nude, short-haired woman (?), crouched to the right on a stool while a nude, bearded man, standing profile to the left assaults her from the other side
Photograph by Maria Daniels, courtesy of the Musée du Louvre

Detail of side B, center: another menage à trois; a nude youth stands profile to the right and thrusts his member into the mouth of a short-haired, nude woman, wearing a narrow taenia on her head, kneeling on a pillow profile to the left; the hand of another man above her back suggests that the missing part of the vase may have depicted her second partner
Photograph by Maria Daniels, courtesy of the Musée du Louvre
Detail of side B, right: the feet of at least two more individuals remain, as does the forepart of a dog, shown profile to the left, emerging from beneath the handle
Photograph by Maria Daniels, courtesy of the Musée du Louvre
